        <p>100 TB ~ 90.9 TiB ~ 10% error</p>
        <p>2009: Snow Leopard --- 1kB = 1000 bytes</p>
        <investigation>
            <statement>
                <p>What are the potential benefits of each of these prefix conventions? Why do you think there is more than one convention?</p>
            </statement>
        </investigation>
        <reading-questions>
            <exercise xml:id="quiz-prefix-1">
                <statement>
                    <p>Find the difference between 3 Mebibyes and 3 Megabytes (in the Apple convention) and express this difference as a percentage of the 3 Megabytes. What is this percent error, rounded to the nearest whole number? Please enter the percentage number only, not the % sign.</p>
                </statement>
                <response/>
            </exercise>
        </reading-questions>
    </section>

    <section xml:id="prefixes-summary">
        <title>Summary</title>
        <p>In this chapter, we covered the following topics:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Memory prefixes and conventions</li>
        </ul>
    </section> 
</chapter>